# Architecture (authoritative invariants)

This is a NestJS 11 + Fastify + TypeORM (**MySQL**) + BullMQ/Redis monorepo,
managed with **npm**. Three apps: admin-api (port 3001, prefix `admin`),
user-api (port 3002, no prefix), worker (no API; optional health 3003). Health
paths: `/admin/health` and `/health`.

## Four layers (one-way dependencies)

```
apps         -> @core, @platform, @domains, @integrations
integrations -> @core, @platform, @domains
domains      -> @core, @platform
platform     -> @core
core         -> @core only (leaf)
```

Each lib lives at `libs/<group>/<name>/src` with an `index.ts` barrel and the
fixed internal layout `entities/dto/vo/mapper/assembler/services/types/constants`.

## The 19 invariants (CI enforces these)

1. Package manager is **npm** — single root `package.json`, no pnpm, no
   `pnpm-workspace.yaml`, no npm `workspaces` field.
2. Database is **MySQL** via `mysql2`; `type: 'mysql'`; `synchronize: false` always.
3. HTTP platform is **Fastify** (`@nestjs/platform-fastify`).
4. Layer dependency direction above is never violated.
5. `domains/*` never import other domains, integrations, or apps.
6. `platform/*` never import domains, integrations, or apps.
7. `core/*` import only `@core`.
8. apps never import each other (admin-api / user-api / worker are isolated).
9. **apps never access a repository.** No `@InjectRepository`, no
   `getRepository`, no `@nestjs/typeorm` in apps. Apps call domain/platform
   **services** only.
10. If a needed domain service/method is missing, **ADD it to the domain lib and
    export it from `index.ts`**, then call it — never query a repo from an app.
11. Controllers return a **VO or `void`**, never an entity.
12. Controllers contain no business logic and no data access. Controllers delegate
    to an **app application service** (`apps/<app>/src/modules/<feature>/<feature>.service.ts`):
    no multi-service orchestration or business branching in a controller. The app
    service composes lib services (never injects a repository, never imports another
    app); HTTP transport (cookies/`@Res`/redirects) stays in the controller and the
    app service returns plain data. Single-call delegations need no app service.
13. `mapper` functions are pure (no DI, no async I/O); `assembler` composes VOs
    and may inject services; `service` never touches HTTP objects.
14. Entities extend `BaseEntity`/`SystemBaseEntity` and set `static uidPrefix`.
15. All schema changes via TypeORM migrations in `/database/migrations`.
16. All HTTP responses use the unified envelope via `TransformInterceptor`;
    errors via `BusinessException` + `AllExceptionsFilter`.
17. Error codes are SCREAMING_SNAKE with a domain prefix; each lib registers its
    own HTTP-status map via `registerErrorCodeHttpStatus`.
18. Long-running / retryable work is enqueued to BullMQ and executed in **worker**
    processors only — never inline in a request.
19. Write endpoints carry `@OperationLogDecorator`; sensitive endpoints carry
    `@RateLimit`; admin endpoints carry `@Permissions`; open routes carry `@Public`.

## The critical rule (repeated because it is the one most often broken)

The app layer must **NOT** access repositories. If a domain service or method
does not exist, **add it to the domain lib and export it** — do not reach into a
repository from an app "to get it working". (Enforced by
`tools/eslint-rules/no-app-repository-import` + `npm run check:boundaries`.)

## Forbidden content

This template contains **no** AI/`ai-fastapi`/`openai`/model-provider/`embedding`/
RAG/`llm` material, and no removed business domains (customer-support, article,
tenant, rule-engine). Keep it that way: such tokens must not appear in code, deps,
docs, env, or docker; reject them in code review.
